# Agent execution (always-on)

Thin reminder. Loop, proof gate, progressive disclosure, validation routing: `AGENTS.md`, `docs/agent_knowledge_base.md`, `docs/agents_quick_reference.md`.

- **Think:** unsafe ambiguity below 95% confidence → stop; evidence from repo docs, code, tests, or scripts (not guesses).
- **Change:** smallest reversible change; every changed line traces to the user request or required validation/doc update.
- **Safety:** destructive/external side effects require current-turn confirmation after listing affected items.
- **Prove:** plan → implement end-to-end → verify → report proof; narrowest honest validation lane.
- **Report:** coding-task closeout includes Files Changed and Follow-up Actions.
- **Stuck:** same failure twice → add durable repo capability (doc, test, fixture, script), not a longer prompt.
- **Seams:** Clean Architecture, Cubit/BLoC, DI, GoRouter.

Copy into project `.cursor/rules/agent-execution.mdc` (gitignored locally). Do not sync to `~/.cursor/rules`.
